Courses are officially ready for accelerated production. Our system, how we do it, and what it will be after improvements over time is knowledge that is ours. Our way is owned by us. Its technically deemed to be classified as Trade Secret. Patents, trademarks, copyright, and the good ol' Trade Secret is the ugly step sibling, and the fourth of four classifications under 'Intellectual Property'. just like the BigMac and its secret sauce - no one knows every step of the process. They own the process of making it and making it in bulk. Thats what we own. Burger Kings of the world are around corner though and we should assume in a 1-2 years the current process will be saturated with similar. For now, this formula is half of the equation. The other half is the process of how we will produce in bulk and producing in bulk on keywords that are discovered before the others realize the demand

And then taking each asset within the bulk, like a two hour mini course for example, and splicing it up into 10 more digital assets like blogs, youtube videos, etc. thats the addition part of the overall equation - another formula where each formula connects and becomes a more complex and even more proprietary in the sense its more difficult to replicate
